{"id": "duc04-testb-23:10#31", "contents": "However, factory owners may have no other choice due to the economic difficulties they are facing. High interest rates and declining sales have made it difficult for them to access credit, and they may be forced to use products to pay the bonus. The president of the Sao Paulo State Association of Small Industries, Joseph Curi, has warned that if banks and the government do not create an emergency credit line, many factories will be left with no option but to use products as payment. Factories that produce clothes, shoes, food, toys, and household appliances are among the most enthusiastic about this idea."}
